msgstr "*link:https://tika.apache.org/[Apache Tika]* 崭露头角——文档内容提取，几乎可以肯定已被应用于代理式和 RAG 工作负载中"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-06-30-quarkus-insights-253-build-analytics.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "AI Extensions: Shifting Landscape"
msgstr "AI 扩展：格局之变"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-06-30-quarkus-insights-253-build-analytics.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "On the AI side, LangChain4j dropped 40% in share, while direct OpenAI integration held or grew. Max and Bruno interpreted this as a maturing pattern: less experimentation with high-level orchestration wrappers, more direct API usage and local model inference."
msgstr "在人工智能领域，LangChain4j 的市场份额下降了 40%，而直接集成 OpenAI 的方案则保持稳定或有所增长。Max 和 Bruno 将此解读为一种日趋成熟的趋势：对高级编排封装层的尝试减少，而直接使用 API 和本地模型推理的趋势则日益增强。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-06-30-quarkus-insights-253-build-analytics.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "AWS-related extensions declined: Lambda usage took a 40% dent year-over-year. Maven download data tells a different story — Amazon extensions have been growing faster than almost anything else — so Bruno suspected the opt-in analytics are capturing a different slice of the AWS user population than the overall download stats."
msgstr "与 AWS 相关的扩展数量有所下降：Lambda 的使用量同比下降了 40%。但 Maven 下载数据却显示出截然不同的情况——亚马逊的扩展增长速度几乎超过了其他所有扩展——因此布鲁诺怀疑，这些基于用户主动选择的分析数据所涵盖的 AWS 用户群体，与整体下载统计数据所反映的群体并不完全一致。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-06-30-quarkus-insights-253-build-analytics.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Apache Camel"
msgstr "Apache Camel"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _posts/2026-06-30-quarkus-insights-253-build-analytics.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "https://camel.apache.org/[Apache Camel] extensions saw notable declines in share. Raw adoption grew slightly, but slower than the overall platform growth, so the relative share fell."
msgstr "link:https://camel.apache.org/[Apache Camel] 扩展的份额出现了显著下滑。其原始采用率虽略有增长，但增速低于平台整体增长，因此相对份额有所下降。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
